The paper deals with solving the Stable Matching Problem with Couples (SMP-C) using a SAT encoding, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores properties such as strategy-proofness, uniqueness, and Pareto optimality, which are topics in Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of SAT encoding also involves techniques from Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses empirical evaluation and analysis, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
